model_explanation: “only gave Sue apples” means apples were given to Sue and to no one else; saying he also gave Rob apples contradicts that.
if only Bill got apples, then Mary did not get apples.
“only gave Mary oranges” means no one other than Mary got oranges; giving Ellen oranges contradicts that.
if only Ellen got apples, then Tom did not get apples.
“only gave Rob bananas” means Rob received nothing but bananas; saying he also got oranges contradicts that.
if Bill received only bananas, he did not receive grapes.
